  "response": "The image of witches flying on broomsticks in front of the full moon is a popular motif in folklore, literature, and media, often associated with Halloween. This imagery finds its roots in centuries-old European folklore where witches were believed to possess the ability to fly, sometimes using broomsticks as a mode of transport. However, from a factual perspective, there is no evidence to support the literal existence of witches flying on broomsticks. This concept remains within the realm of myth and fantasy.",
